law.text: Each warehouseman shall keep a register, which shall contain a list and description of all property stored in his warehouse; the name and residence of the owner, if known, the time when the goods were received, and the amount of charges on the goods.
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 4777.
